txt.en:
'Look at all this rubbish!

'Lugbúrz goes down, and it takes half of Cirith Ungol with it! Ah, that always was the way of the Eye, wasn't it?

'Well, if I'm to keep serving here, it's got to look a bit more imposing -- not like a rockslide that happened to shape itself into a Tower!

'Garn! Clear some of the debris, Silent One!'
Following Sauron's downfall, Danghát has become frustrated with the amount of wreckage and debris in Cirith Ungol.
You have cleared a great deal of debris from Cirith Ungol. It seems to you that Danghát is unlikely to complain to Captain Róglarg as so much of Cirith Ungol is in disrepair.
Debris can be found throughout Cirith Ungol.\n\nDanghát has asked you to help clear debris from Cirith Ungol.
You have cleared a great deal of debris from Cirith Ungol.
